The optimal production schedule is shown below under get.variables(lps.model). The total cost of meeting the next six months of demand on time is $10,660.

Choose: x1, x2, ., x6 - Regular
y1, y2, ., y6 - Overtime
z2, z3, ., z6 - Carry-over into month i
Min sum(7xi + 11yi + zi)
S.t.
xi <= 200
yi <= 100
x1 + y1 >= 200
x2 + y2 + z2 >= 260
x3 + y3 + z3 >= 240
x4 + y4 + z4 >= 340
x5 + y5 + z5 >= 190
x6 + y6 + z6 >= 150
x1 + y1 - z2 = 200
x2 + y2 + z2 - z3 = 260
x3 + y3 + z3 - z4 = 240
x4 + y4 + z4 - z5 = 340
x5 + y5 + z5 - z6 = 190
x6 + y6 + z6 = 150

library(lpSolveAPI)

lps.model <- make.lp(0, 17)

for (x in (1:6)) {
  xt <- rep(0,17)
  xt[x] <- 1
  add.constraint(lps.model, xt, "<=", 200)
}

for (y in (7:12)) {
  xt <- rep(0,17)
  xt[y] <- 1
  add.constraint(lps.model, xt, "<=", 100)
}

demand = c(200,260,240,340,190,150)
for (i in (1:6)) {
  xt <- rep(0,17)
  xt[i] <- 1
  xt[i+6] <- 1
  if (i > 1) {
    xt[i+11] <- 1
  }
  add.constraint(lps.model, xt, ">=", demand[i])
}

for (i in (1:6)) {
  xt <- rep(0,17)
  xt[i] <- 1
  xt[i+6] <- 1
  if (i < 6) {
    xt[i+12] <- -1
  }
  if (i > 1) {
    xt[i+11] <- 1
  }
  add.constraint(lps.model, xt, "=", demand[i])
}

set.objfn(lps.model, c(rep(7,6),rep(11,6),rep(1,5)))
solve(lps.model)
